In addition to the bundled faces above, text editing can resolve ~30 common
Google Fonts (Roboto, Open Sans, Lato, Montserrat, Poppins, Inter, …) by fetching
their TTF on demand from the google/fonts repository via the jsdelivr CDN, plus
Noto Sans and Noto Sans SC as broad Unicode / CJK fallbacks. These are likewise
SIL Open Font License 1.1 (OFL-1.1) and are not redistributed in this repository —
they are fetched at runtime only when a document actually uses one.

Tiny font subsets are vendored as TEST fixtures only (not part of the shipped
application), each covering just the glyphs its test uses:
  - tools/render-parity/fixtures/noto-cjk-test.ttf — a subset of Noto Sans SC
    (OFL-1.1, Copyright The Noto Project Authors), ~5 KB.
  - tools/render-parity/fixtures/roboto-latin-test.ttf — a subset of Roboto
    (OFL-1.1/Apache-2.0, Copyright The Roboto Project Authors), Latin only.

Font subsetting/embedding uses @pdf-lib/fontkit (MIT).
